## KEY CONSTRAINTS & DECISIONS

### Business Model
- **Revenue Mix**: Subscriptions (base) + Amazon commissions (upside)
- **Subscription independence**: Client pays same regardless of results
- **Amazon risk**: 3-month payment delay, can terminate anytime
- **Pricing**: €50/month or €400/year per country
- **Multi-country**: €100/month flat for 3+ countries

### Technical Constraints
- **Amazon Associates**: No API for affiliate results (manual weekly report upload)
- **Dashboard complexity**: Start simple (clicks + orders), expand later
- **CRM**: Google Sheets only (no Pipedrive, no HubSpot)
- **Payments**: Flexible (Stripe, PayPal, Kartra - whatever works)
- **Outreach**: 90%+ automation (AI calling) except existing clients

### Automation Levels
- **Site creation**: 95% automated (2 min subdomain creation manual)
- **Content generation**: 100% AI (Claude API)
- **Seller outreach**: 90% automated (AI calling + webinar)
- **Payment processing**: 100% automated (webhooks)
- **Patronage activation**: 100% automated (on payment confirmation)
- **Client reporting**: Semi-automated (weekly manual report upload)

## CRITICAL WORKFLOWS

### Workflow 1: New Site Launch
```
Research → Competition Check → Product Selection → Site Build → 
Content Generation → Traffic Building → Ranking → First Orders → 
Seller Contact
```

### Workflow 2: Seller Onboarding (Automated)
```
AI Cold Call → Qualification → EverWebinar Invitation → 
Webinar Attended → Payment Page → Payment Received → 
Invoice Generated → Patronage Activated → Dashboard Access Sent
```

### Workflow 3: Subscription Management
```
Payment Received → Enable Patronage Features (logo, contact, exclusive products) →
Client Dashboard Access → Weekly Report Update → Renewal Reminder (if monthly)

Subscription Expired → Remove Patronage Features → 
Revert to Multi-Product Display → Site Continues Earning Commissions
```

### Workflow 4: Crisis Management
```
Issue Detected → Automated Alert → Site Temporarily Disabled (maintenance page) →
Client Notification Email → Internal Dashboard Alert → Manual Review →
Fix Applied → Site Re-enabled → Post-mortem Report
```

